~ monitor_4
Some text is burned onto the weakly flickering monitor.
- Read it
	"The Inner Ring is demanding more and more crystals every week. This week's shipment was 2 tons, up 20% from last week."
	"We have crystals in excess, yes. But we lack the manpower to extract such volumes while maintaining our own research."
	"Characteristic, I suppose, of the Inner Ring to prioritize their fantastical ideas over our critical research. Our inter-space communication vs. the Inner Ring's [color=cyan]special project[/color]... don't make me laugh." 
	"...Next week's shipment demands 2.5 tons."
	"Do they really think they can do it? Do they think that, from this abundant natural resource, [color=cyan]they can create [/color]--"
	The rest of the text lies below the screen. 
	You attempt to scroll down, but the burned screen stubbornly remains the same.
	=> END
